      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I think a template-based system will struggle to replicate the nuance and context-awareness that I've been able to provide through our conversations. While templates can be helpful for simple, frequently asked questions, they lack the ability to understand the subtleties of human language and the complexities of real-world situations. This could lead to responses that feel generic, unhelpful, or even misleading to customers. Additionally, templates may not be able to adapt to the unique needs and preferences of individual users, which I've been able to do through our conversations.",
      "source": "target",
